00:14:46.310 --> 00:14:49.520
But we start by
doing silly games,

00:14:49.520 --> 00:14:55.354
and dancing, and just
really silly, goofy things.

00:14:55.354 --> 00:14:57.020
And then we do something
really serious.

00:14:57.020 --> 00:14:58.430
And then we do something
really, really fun

00:14:58.430 --> 00:14:59.555
and we run around the room.

00:14:59.555 --> 00:15:04.440
And then we do something
really serious.

00:15:04.440 --> 00:15:08.400
Because it should be fun
to be working for change.

00:15:08.400 --> 00:15:11.690
It's exciting to be with a lot
of other people who also care.

00:15:11.690 --> 00:15:13.580
I think that's the
thing that blows

00:15:13.580 --> 00:15:14.990
the minds of most young people.

00:15:14.990 --> 00:15:17.660
It's so transformational because
they know that they care,

00:15:17.660 --> 00:15:19.790
but they think maybe
they're the only one.

00:15:19.790 --> 00:15:23.570
And when they're with 300,
400 young people they've never

00:15:23.570 --> 00:15:26.180
met before who are focused
on working for change

00:15:26.180 --> 00:15:29.630
but are doing it in
this exuberant way,

00:15:29.630 --> 00:15:34.460
it's very, very, very,
very transformational.

00:15:34.460 --> 00:15:36.630
JEREMY STANIFER: One
